1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
This video demonstrates how MetricMind integrates with LinkedIn to analyze digital presence signals and publish insights.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
MetricMind is a digital intelligence platform that detects early signals across websites and social platforms.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Users begin by logging into MetricMind and connecting their LinkedIn account.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
MetricMind uses the official LinkedIn OAuth 2.0 flow to request authorization from the user.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:28,000
After authentication, MetricMind retrieves basic profile information such as name and email.

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
This confirms the LinkedIn identity connection and activates the MetricMind signal layer.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Next, the user analyzes a website to detect publicly observable digital signals.

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:46,000
MetricMind evaluates signals such as website presence, social links, and overall digital observability.

9
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:52,000
These signals help organizations understand their digital footprint across platforms.

10
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:58,000
MetricMind allows users to share intelligence insights directly to LinkedIn.

11
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Here the user initiates the publishing flow from within the MetricMind platform.

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
MetricMind prepares an insight that can be shared through the LinkedIn network.

13
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,000
The LinkedIn post composer opens, allowing the user to review the content before publishing.

14
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:22,000
The user can edit the message, confirm the audience, and publish the insight.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Once published, the post appears on the user's LinkedIn feed.

16
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Other LinkedIn members can interact with the post through reactions and comments.

17
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
MetricMind analyzes these engagement signals to understand how insights spread across professional networks.

18
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:46,000
MetricMind is designed to support organizations that manage LinkedIn pages.

19
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Page administrators can publish insights and monitor engagement signals from their organization.

20
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:58,000
MetricMind also tracks post performance indicators such as reactions, comments, and visibility signals.

21
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:04,000
These capabilities enable community managers to better understand engagement and digital visibility.

22
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:10,000
This concludes the demonstration of the MetricMind LinkedIn integration and its community management use cases.


